args: Pardon me, Luca, but might I\nask you a question?
That's weird—no one asks me questions!\nBut sure, fire away.
Why are you always dressed in costume?
I'm trying to figure out why you are\nalways wearing those rabbit ears.
I think you just broke my brain.
OW! Don't yank the merchandise, Cleo!
Luca and I are a race called sylvans.\nThe long ears come standard for us.
Pray forgive me for this\nterrible misunderstanding.
We don't have such things in my world,\nso I never thought they might be real.
When I mentioned it to Prince Alfonse,\nhe suggested they might be some\nmanner of spring festival costume.
Hey, no worries. If I didn't know me,\nI'd be curious, too!
Yeah, they do that. It's so we can hear\nstuff that's far away and junk.
Would you care to touch his ears?
Are you sure? They're ever so soft\nand fluffy and boofy.
I'm fine if you wanna touch 'em,\nbut you do you.
Are you certain you don't mind?
Well, in that case... *pet*\nBY THE GODS! SUCH FLUFFINESS!
They are so soft and warm...
They truly are like real bunny ears.
Pffft... AAAAH HA HA HA! S-STOP!\nSPARE MEEEEE!
Oh dear. Perhaps he was offended when\nI said they were like actual bunny ears.
I think you were just tickling him.
Oh dear. What a mess.\nStill, they were SO soft...
And you are also a sylvan, Cleo?
Yes. Though my ears are covered,\nso you can't touch them.
Er, no. That's not why I asked.
Heya, Cleo! Did something happen?\nLuca just ran by me laughing like\na crazy person.
We attempted intra-world communication.\nIt was something of a failure.
You did who with the what now?
Your wings are as beautiful as ever, Notte.
Yeah, they ARE pretty great, huh?
I take it you and Notte are\nalready friends, Fjorm?
Dang right! We're basically besties,\neven though I'm the first faerie she's\never seen.
In my world, faeries are the stuff of\nfolklore and cradle tales.
To actually speak with one is like\nsomething out of a dream.

Oh yeah, keep the praise coming, sister!
Although I'm also SUPER stoked to be
chatting it up with a princess who came
here through a time portal or whatever.
Hey, guys. Sorry about that!\nAll that tickling sent me runnin'.
Aw, it ain't no thing. But if you're THAT\ncurious about sylvans, you should come\nto our Vernal Banquet next year.
All the sylvans on the continent gather\ntogether to celebrate the new spring.
Plus, everybody brings a local delicacy,\nso you can stuff your face until your\npants split!
If you swing by, I can introduce you\nto my little sister, Sarisse.
...I'm sorry. I was merely reminded\nof my own sister just now.
You have a sister, huh? Maybe she can\npop through the ol' space hole and\nwe can meet her someday!
Oh, she's a curious one, all right.\nWild horses couldn't keep her from\nthis Vernal Banquet of yours.
Then you TOTALLY gotta get her to come!
Yes, it sounds like she would enjoy it.
Alas, I know not how long I will be able\nto remain in your world.
But if I am still here in the spring,\nI will certainly attend your festival.
